column4: "How Deep is the Ocean - solo piano"
"Played in real time - dougmck@pipeline.com.au\012"
"Lots of ideas borrowed from Roger Kellaway's version on his 'Maybeck Hall' recital solo CD. \012"
"Opening phrase LH & RH in unison"
"On Am7b5 descending run - easy to execute"
"Resolves by surrounding 3rd of Gm"
"On Gm7 arpeggiated perfect 4ths - C
"On Gb7 diminished half/whole step runn"
"On Fm7 - dorian (Eb major scale) ascending"
"continued on Fm7 - descending Fm pentatonic scale"
"Finishes on root of Bb7 chord"
"On Bb7b9 easy 2 handed ascending run - LH on Black
"Continue on Bb7 descending sequence of notes based on diminished scale"
"Parallel tenths rising to tonic (DbMaj
"On Ab7 - whole tone scale - more or less randomly struck notes from the 6 notes"
"Sustain pedal down through all this Whole Tone stuff"
"One of the ways to harmonise the modulation back to Cm"
"D/Bb Db/A Ab6/9 G7"
"Bass figure based on Blues scale"
"On Db7#11 Whole Tone Scale again with sustain pedal down-  LH plays Black notes
"No turn-around bar - straight back to start"
"'Who's a dirty rascal?' quote"
"Run on F7b9 combining alternately diminished chord and chromatic scale"
"On C7 Whole/half dim scale - no pedal"
"On F13 descending run with changes of direction"
"Ending based on cycle of 5ths harmony finishing on Eb"
"MIDI 2"
